Hi Wladimyr

You need to install python-devel.

Ricky

> Hi Guys
>
> We are experimenting a trouble during cantera 1.7.0 installation. Our
> machine is a i386 based running Suse linux 10.2. We installed python
> numarray and gfortran. preconfig and make commands run without
> problem. But during "make install" command under root, the following
> message appears and stop:
> .
> .
> .
> cd Cantera/python; make install
> make[1]: Entering directory
> `/home/fernando/usr/cantera/src/cantera-1.7.0/Cantera/python'
> (/usr/bin/python setup.py install
> --prefix="/usr/local/share/cantera-1.7.0")
> running install
> running install
> setup.py:104: DeprecationWarning: raising a string exception is deprecated
>   raise 'Error encountered while building or installing the Cantera
> CTI file preprocessor!'
> Traceback (most recent call last):
>   File "setup.py", line 104, in <module>
>     raise 'Error encountered while building or installing the Cantera
> CTI file preprocessor!'
> Error encountered while building or installing the Cantera CTI file
> preprocessor!
> make[1]: *** [install] Error 1
> make[1]: Leaving directory
> `/home/fernando/usr/cantera/src/cantera-1.7.0/Cantera/python'
> make: *** [python-install] Error 2
>
> Can somebody help us?
>
>
> Many tanks in advance
>
> Wladimyr
>
>
>
